gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Raptors 107, Rockets 104
gameRecap.excerpt: The Raptors held off the Rockets despite being outscored 33-19 in the final frame, as they win 107-104. Immanuel Quickley had a game-high with 25 points as RJ Barrett (21 points, five rebounds, seven assists) and Scottie Barnes (13 points, 10 rebounds, eight assists) totaled 34 points. Dillon Brooks (20 points) and Cam Whitmore (20 points, three rebounds) led the Rockets in the loss. Toronto wins their second in a row to improve to 19-33 while the Rockets move to 23-28.
